Theorem (lemmainverse):
  for all v0, (if v0 is a map and v0 is injective then for all v1, (if v1 is an element of the domain of v0 then (the value of v0 under v1 is an element of the domain of \inv{ v0 } and the value of \inv{ v0 } under the value of v0 under v1 is equal to v1)))
Proof:
  v is an element of the domain of f
  the value of f under v is an element of the domain of \inv{ f }
  Proof:
    \range( f ) is equal to the domain of \inv{ f }
  Qed.
  w is equal to the value of \inv{ f } under the value of f under v
  the value of f under w is equal to the value of f under v
  Proof:
    the value of f under w is equal to the value of f under the value of \inv{ f } under the value of f under v
    the value of f under the value of \inv{ f } under the value of f under v is equal to the value of f under v
  Qed.
  w is equal to v
  Proof:
    f is injective
  Qed.
Qed.

